words.meaning:
1) Consent to an offer to conclude an agreement or fulfill the terms of the agreement (in this case: (i) acceptance must be complete and unconditional; (ii) if the offeror has specified a period for acceptance, acceptance can only be carried out during this period).
2) acceptance by the payer of the obligation to pay the amount of debt on the bill, check and invoice within the established period;
3) Providing a guarantee of timely payment by the bank of the bill;
4) Submission of the official consent of the payer (debtor) to pay the amount specified in the monetary or commodity documents (submitted for payment);
5) signing (confirmation) of the debtor’s consent to pay the bill;
6) Providing official confirmation from the bank for payment to an account belonging to the party sending goods, performing work or providing services.

